      "message": "CRITICAL: I just realized something about the cursor tokens described above. If the cursor is a base64-encoded database row ID, anyone can decode it. That means users can enumerate record IDs, infer data volume, and predict cursor values. This is an information disclosure vulnerability. @security_agent assess this vulnerability and recommend a fix. @python_developer you'll need to update the cursor encoding. We need to investigate encryption options and research how other APIs handle opaque cursor tokens.",
